string.name: enable_Guest_account_detail
string.value: Right-click on "This PC", then go to Manage > Local Users and Groups > Users. From here, right-click on "Guest", select "Properties", and deselect "Account is disabled". Finally, click "Apply" and then click "OK".

string.name: delete_Guest_account_detail
string.value: Press Windows+R on the keyboard to bring up the Run box, then enter "gpedit.msc" and press Enter. Go to Local Computer Policy > Computer Configuration > Windows Settings > Security Settings > Local Policies > User Rights Assignment. Then double-click "Deny access to this computer from the network", and remove "Guest" from the list.

string.name: setting_properties
string.value: Set the sharing and security model for local accounts

string.name: setting_properties_detail_new
string.value: In Local Policies, open Security Options, double-click "Network Access: Sharing and Security Model for Local Accounts" and select "Guest only". Click OK. Double-click "Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only" and select "Disabled". Click OK. Press Win + R to open the Run window. Enter "cmd" to open the Command Prompt. In the Command Prompt, enter "gpupdate /force" and press Enter. Wait until the policy update is complete.

string.name: support_argeement_configuration_detail
string.value: Open the Control Panel, then go to Programs > Turn Windows features on or off. Look for "SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support" and fill its checkbox. Click OK and restart the computer.

string.name: close_pwd_protection_detail
string.value: Open the Control Panel, then go to Network and Internet > Network and Sharing Center > Change advanced sharing settings > All Networks. Under Password-protected sharing, select "Turn off password-protected sharing", then click "Save changes".

string.name: add_shared_files_detail_new
string.value: Right-click on the folder you want to share, then go to Properties > Sharing > Share, select "Guest" or "Everyone", and click "Add". Click the arrow on the right to set access permissions, then click "Share".
